{
  "texts": [
    "It is calculated using the following equation: Page 19 of 36 41",
    "where Φ(⋅) is a function that derives the volume occupied by the variable input in the MAPF environment.",
    "In specific, it calculates the volume occupied by all agents Φ(A), the dynamic obstacles Φ(O dyn), the entire map environment Φ(V), and the static obstacles Φ(O static).",
    "For instance, in a grid map environment with N agents and M dynamic, and K static obstacles, Crowdedness can be simply computed as N+M |V|-K.",
    "Figure 9 shows examples of calculating Crowdedness in 2D and 3D environments."
  ]
